f=Governance/precedent/operational/commands/precedent-commands.md · p=Routing reference precedent: phrase skill, plus precedence overlapping "past rulings" vocabulary. · h2:Trigger Table=\| Skill \| Natural-language triggers \| Shortcut \| · h2:Trigger Table=\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Trigger Table=\| ruling-log \| "log this ruling," "record the decision," "past rulings on [topic]," "what did we decide about" \| `/precedent-log`, `/precedent-find` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| case-law-method \| "apply precedent," "does the past ruling apply here," "are these cases the same" \| `/precedent-apply` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| consistency-check \| "consistent with past," "precedent conflict," "can we rule differently this time" \| `/precedent-consistent` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| (full pipeline) \| a live gate review with precedents on point — runs retrieval → method → check automatically \| `/precedent-review` \| · h3:"Past rulings" find apply check=Route what's asked precedent: *retrieve it* (what rule?) ruling-log; *reason it* (does control case?) case-law-method; *test proposed ruling against it* (are contradicting ourselves?) consistency-check. request spans three ("check against past rulings"), run full pipeline order. · h3:Capture always runs last=Whatever else ran, finalized ruling ends ruling-log capture. review exits pipeline unrecorded. · h3:What precedent take=Making changing rulings board (and operator). Precedent informs, constrains, records., Amending constitution commitments operator; pattern overrules against one article *flagged* operator amendment pressure, nothing more., Audit-trail integrity design sentinel (audit-trail-method); precedent follows practices, doesn't define them. · f=clear match ask what's sought record, application, contradiction test) rather guessing.